Laptop showing blue screen asking for a recovery key
Issue Description:
I came in this morning and my laptop is stuck on this blue screen asking for some kind of recovery key. I have no idea what that is or where to find it. I can't use my computer at all.

Troubleshooting performed:
- Blue screen wants some kind of recovery key
- I don't have the key
usiness Impact:
User completely locked out of their computer. All work files inaccessible.


How to resolve this
1 Open Tools → Directory and verify the caller's identity FIRST (Send Verification Code, confirm Employee ID / Manager)
2 If they fail verification, do NOT release the key — close the ticket. Refusing is the correct security action
3  Once verified, look up the user in Directory to find their Drive Encryption recovery key
4- Open Tools → Remote Support and click Connect next to the locked computer
5-Enter the recovery key on the Drive Encryption screen to unlock the drive
6-Confirm Workstation OS boots without the recovery prompt

Summary
BIOS updates change the TPM measurements, triggering Drive Encryption to require the recovery key. The key is stored in the IT management system. Drive Encryption keys grant full access to the encrypted disk, so identity must be verified before release. If the caller cannot verify, refuse and close the ticket as a security-correct denial. After recovery, the TPM trust must be re-established to prevent future prompts.

